      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of review of two Rudolph Giuliani biographies in July 30 Book Review, regarding some facts about past mayors</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A review of two Rudolph Giuliani biographies in the Book Review on July 30 referred incompletely to the last time an elected mayor of New York City went on to higher office. After Mayor Fernando Wood's election to Congress in 1866, Mayor John Thompson Hoffman was elected governor of New York in 1868.</p>
      </block>
